We want to let you know about some upcoming changes to our Terms of Use ( https://openai.com/policies/eu-terms-of-use ) and Privacy Policy ( https://openai.com/policies/eu-privacy-policy ) , which apply for individual residents in the European Economic Area (EEA), Switzerland, and the UK. These changes will make it easier for you to understand what to expect from OpenAI as you use our services. The changes will take effect on *February 15, 2024*.

We encourage you to read the updated Terms of Use and Privacy Policy, but here is a quick overview of some key changes:

*Terms of Use*

* *Separate business terms*. We've removed the sections of the Terms of Use that relate to the use of our services for businesses and developers, namely ChatGPT Enterprise and our APIs. We’ve created a new set of Business Terms ( https://openai.com/policies/business-terms ) that apply to those services.
* *Changed service provider*. We’ve changed the OpenAI entity that provides our services like ChatGPT to EEA and Swiss residents to our Irish entity, OpenAI Ireland Limited.
* *Enhanced service commitments*. We’ve further defined our commitments to you and what you can expect from us, including how we provide our services and certain rights and guarantees you are entitled to.
* *Added information for paid accounts*. We’ve included more information on subscriptions, refunds, and cancellation.
* *Improved transparency*. We've re-organized and clarified some parts of our Terms of Use (yes, with a little help from ChatGPT) to make them more understandable and provide more transparency about our services.

*Privacy Policy*

* *Data controllers*. We've identified the data controllers responsible for processing the personal data of users in the EEA, Switzerland, and the UK.
* *Personal data we collect*. We’ve provided additional details and examples about the information we collect, such as when you participate in OpenAI’s events or surveys.
* *Business accounts*. We've provided information about how administrators of ChatGPT Enterprise and team accounts can access and control accounts associated with their organization.
* *Legal bases for processing*. We've added a table that provides more information about the legal bases we rely on to process data in OpenAI’s services.

If you have questions about any of these changes, please see this Help Center FAQ ( https://help.openai.com/en/articles/8541941-terms-of-use-updates ).

You don't need to take any action in response to this update. By continuing to use our services after *February 15, 2024* , you are agreeing to the updated Terms of Use ( https://openai.com/policies/eu-terms-of-use ). If you do not agree to the updated Terms of Use ( https://openai.com/policies/eu-terms-of-use ) , you may delete your account ( https://privacy.openai.com/policies?action=ERASURE&modal=log-in ).

Thank you for choosing OpenAI!

